These predictions were not taken from the three famous Sibylline books said· to have been pur· , chased by King Tarquin, for those had been destroyed twenty years before, at the time of the burning of the capitol Various other Sibylline books were, however, soon after collected from different parts of Italy and Greece. ln one of these was found a prediction which was interpreted to mean that three members of the Cornelian gens should rule at Rome. Lentulus claimed that the three Cornelii were Publius Cornelius Cinna, notorious for his tyranny and cruelty, Lucius Cornelius Sulla, the famous dictator, and himself, Publius Cornelius Lentulus.
